The article discusses a series of measures announced by President Barack Obama to promote biofuels and clean coal as part of his strategy to increase US energy independence and create a new economy based on clean energy. The measures include the Environmental Protection Agency implementing a long-term renewable fuel standard, the Department of Agriculture proposing a rule for the Biomass Crop Assistance Program, and the Biofuels Interagency Working Group releasing its first report on promoting sustainable biofuel development. Additionally, President Obama announced the creation of an Interagency Task Force on Carbon Capture and Storage to accelerate the development and implementation of clean coal technology. The article highlights the potential for job creation and economic growth through the production of biomass and biofuels, as well as the importance of reducing dependence on foreign oil and addressing climate change.